<command>
<name>validate ossi user and password</name>
<description>Validate the user and password for adhoc needs</description>
<type>Local Syntax</type>

<argument datatype="string" name="usr_id"></argument>
<argument datatype="string" name="usr_pswd"></argument>

<transaction>new</transaction>

<local-syntax>
<![CDATA[
/*
* Change Log
* Initial Check In
* Kent.Zhao - 10731
*/
try
{
   save session variable where name = 'uc_ossi_called_for_validate_pswd' and value = '1'
   ;
   login user
}
finally
{
   rollback
}

]]>
</local-syntax>

<documentation>
<remarks>
Idea is that we call login user.  If it succeeds great.  Otherwise caller can trap the error and see
</remarks>

<retrows>0</retrows>

<retcol name="n/a" type="COMTYP_CHAR">See SQL</retcol>


<exception value="eOK">The command completed successfully.</exception>

</documentation>


</command>
